        "auditory": "I hear breath fracture into sobs-wet, uneven pulls that keep failing halfway through. If words come, they arrive broken, swallowed, reshaped by the body trying not to fall apart.",
        "tactile": "Someone starts to shake in waves-small at first, then unstoppable. Their body has that unmistakable grief rhythm: tight, trembling pulses like the whole frame is trying to hold itself together."
